---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Legal"
  description="Legal information, terms, and policies for Finnoybu: Salt and Silence."
>
  <div class="max-w-shell mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1
        class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight text-ink mb-4"
        style="font-feature-settings: 'ss01'"
      >
        Terms &amp; Policies
      </h1>
      <p class="font-serif text-sm text-ink-muted mb-12">Last updated: May 16, 2026</p>

      <nav class="mb-12 p-6 bg-bg-elev border border-rule-soft rounded-lg">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-3 text-[10px]">On this page</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 font-sans text-sm">
          <li><a href="#copyright" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Copyright</a></li>
          <li><a href="#terms-of-use" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Terms of Use</a></li>
          <li><a href="#privacy-policy" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#data-deletion" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Data Deletion</a></li>
          <li><a href="#acceptable-use" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Acceptable Use</a></li>
          <li><a href="#accessibility" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Accessibility</a></li>
          <li><a href="#cookie-policy" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Cookie Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#disclaimer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Disclaimer</a></li>
          <li><a href="#dmca" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">DMCA &amp; Takedown</a></li>
          <li><a href="#impressum" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi transition-colors">Impressum</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>

      <div class="prose-memoir">
        <section id="copyright" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Copyright</h2>
          <p>
            © 2026 Finnoybu Press. All rights reserved. The text of
            "Finnoybu: Salt and Silence" and all accompanying
            illustrations are the property of Finnoybu Press and may not be
            reproduced, distributed, or transmitted in any form without prior
            written permission.
          </p>
          <p>
            "Finnoybu: Salt and Silence" is a work of fiction by
            E.&nbsp;A. Westbo. Names, characters, places, and incidents are
            the product of the author's imagination. Any resemblance
            to actual persons, living or dead, is coincidental.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="terms-of-use" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Terms of Use</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing <strong>fiction.finnoybu.com</strong> ("the Site"),
            operated by Finnoybu Press ("we," "us," "our"),
            you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not
            use the Site. We may update these terms at any time by posting a revised version;
            your continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>

          <h3>Accounts</h3>
          <p>
            You may create an account using email and password or through a supported
            social-sign-in provider (Google, Facebook, Apple, or GitHub). You are responsible
            for keeping your credentials confidential and for all activity under your account.
            Accounts span <strong>finnoybu.com</strong> — signing in on fiction.finnoybu.com
            also signs you in on memoirs.finnoybu.com (cross-subdomain session). Accounts are
            for personal, non-commercial use only. You must be at least 13 years of age to
            create an account.
          </p>

          <h3>Purchases</h3>
          <p>
            Digital downloads (PDF/ePub) are processed through Stripe. All sales are
            final. If you experience a technical issue with your purchase, contact us
            at <a href="mailto:finnoybu@gmail.com">finnoybu@gmail.com</a> and we will
            work to resolve it.
          </p>

          <h3>User-generated content</h3>
          <p>
            You retain ownership of any bookmarks and annotations you create on the Site.
          </p>

          <h3>Termination</h3>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these
            terms or the Acceptable Use policy. You may delete your account at any
            time by contacting us (see <a href="#data-deletion">Data Deletion</a>).
          </p>

          <h3>Limitation of liability</h3>
          <p>
            The Site is provided "as is." To the fullest extent permitted
            by law, Finnoybu Press shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental,
            or consequential damages arising from your use of the Site.
          </p>

          <h3>Governing law</h3>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Virginia,
            United States, without regard to conflict-of-law principles.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="privacy-policy" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p>
            Finnoybu Press ("we," "us," "our")
            operates <strong>fiction.finnoybu.com</strong>. This Privacy Policy explains
            what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding that data.
          </p>

          <h3>What we collect</h3>

          <h4>Account information</h4>
          <p>
            When you create an account, we collect your <strong>email address</strong> and,
            if you sign in with Google / Facebook / Apple / GitHub, your <strong>name</strong>
            and <strong>profile picture</strong> as provided by that service. If you create
            an account with email and password, we store a securely hashed version of your
            password — we never store passwords in plain text.
          </p>

          <h4>Reading activity</h4>
          <p>
            If you are signed in, we store your <strong>reading progress</strong> (which
            chapter you are reading, your scroll position, and the percentage read) so you
            can resume where you left off across devices.
          </p>

          <h4>User-generated content</h4>
          <p>
            We store <strong>bookmarks</strong> (chapter, position, and optional label)
            and <strong>annotations</strong> (selected text and your notes)
            that you create while using the Site.
          </p>

          <h4>Purchase information</h4>
          <p>
            When you purchase a digital download, we record the <strong>product purchased</strong>,
            <strong> amount paid</strong>, <strong>currency</strong>, and a
            <strong> Stripe session identifier</strong>. We do not receive or store your
            payment card details — those are handled entirely by Stripe.
          </p>

          <h4>Browser storage</h4>
          <p>
            We store your <strong>reading preferences</strong> (theme, font size) and
            <strong> cookie-consent status</strong> in your browser's local storage.
            This data never leaves your device unless you are signed in, in which case
            reading progress is synced to our servers.
          </p>

          <h3>How we use your data</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>To provide and maintain the reading experience (progress sync, bookmarks, annotations)</li>
            <li>To process purchases and deliver digital downloads</li>
            <li>To send transactional emails (sign-in links)</li>
            <li>To understand how readers use the Site in aggregate (anonymous analytics)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal data with third
            parties for advertising or marketing purposes. We do <strong>not</strong> send
            marketing or promotional emails.
          </p>

          <h3>Third-party services</h3>
          <p>We share data with the following services, solely to operate the Site:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Cloudflare</strong> (hosting, database, file storage) — hosts the
              Site on Cloudflare Pages, stores your account information, reading progress,
              bookmarks, annotations, errata reports, and purchase records in a Cloudflare
              D1 database, and serves paid downloads from Cloudflare R2.{' '}
              <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Cloudflare Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Amazon Web Services (Simple Email Service)</strong> — sends sign-in,
              verification, and password-reset emails on our behalf. AWS receives only the
              destination email and the contents of the message.{' '}
              <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                AWS Privacy Notice
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Stripe</strong> (payment processing) — receives your email
              address and processes payment card details directly.{' '}
              <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Stripe Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Google</strong> (OAuth sign-in) — if you sign in with Google, we
              receive your email, name, and profile picture from Google.{' '}
              <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Google Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Meta / Facebook</strong> (OAuth sign-in) — if you sign in with
              Facebook, we receive your email, name, and profile picture from Meta.{' '}
              <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Meta Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Apple</strong> (OAuth sign-in) — if you sign in with Apple, we
              receive your email (real or relay) and name as provided.{' '}
              <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Apple Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>GitHub</strong> (OAuth sign-in) — if you sign in with GitHub, we
              receive your email, username, and profile picture.{' '}
              <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                GitHub Privacy Statement
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Data retention</h3>
          <p>
            We retain your account data and associated content (bookmarks, annotations, reading
            progress) for as long as your account is active. Purchase records are retained
            indefinitely for tax and accounting purposes. If you delete your account, all
            personal data is removed except purchase records, which are anonymized.
          </p>

          <h3>Your rights</h3>
          <p>You have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access</strong> your personal data — contact us and we will provide a copy of the data we hold about you.</li>
            <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate data — contact us with the change.</li>
            <li><strong>Delete</strong> your data — see <a href="#data-deletion">Data Deletion</a> below.</li>
            <li><strong>Export</strong> your data — contact us and we will provide your data in a portable format.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            If you are located in the European Economic Area, you have additional rights under
            the GDPR, including the right to restrict processing and the right to lodge a
            complaint with your local data protection authority. If you are a California
            resident, the CCPA grants you similar rights. To exercise any of these rights,
            contact us at <a href="mailto:finnoybu@gmail.com">finnoybu@gmail.com</a>.
          </p>

          <h3>Children's privacy</h3>
          <p>
            The Site is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
            personal data from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13 has
            provided us with personal data, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
          </p>

          <h3>Changes to this policy</h3>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on
            this page with an updated "last updated" date. Material changes
            will be communicated by email to registered users.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="data-deletion" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Data Deletion</h2>
          <h3>Deletion by request</h3>
          <p>
            You may request deletion by emailing
            <a href="mailto:finnoybu@gmail.com"> finnoybu@gmail.com</a> with the subject
            line "Delete my account." Please send the request from the email
            address associated with your account. We will process your request
            within <strong>30 days</strong> and confirm by email once complete.
          </p>
          <p>
            Deletion removes your user account, sign-in records, reading progress,
            bookmarks, and annotations. Purchase records are anonymized (retaining only
            the transaction amount and date for accounting purposes).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="acceptable-use" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>When using the Site, you agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Copy, reproduce, distribute, or publicly display the manuscript text or
              illustrations without prior written permission from Finnoybu Press.
            </li>
            <li>
              Use automated tools (bots, scrapers, crawlers) to access the Site or
              download content in bulk.
            </li>
            <li>
              Attempt to gain unauthorized access to other users' accounts or data.
            </li>
            <li>
              Interfere with the operation of the Site, including introducing malware
              or overloading the server with excessive requests.
            </li>
            <li>
              Submit annotations or other user-generated content that
              is abusive, threatening, defamatory, or otherwise objectionable.
            </li>
            <li>
              Use the Site for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable
              local, state, national, or international law.
            </li>
            <li>
              Create multiple accounts for the purpose of circumventing restrictions
              or abusing the service.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate this policy,
            with or without notice, at our sole discretion.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="accessibility" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Accessibility</h2>
          <p>
            We are committed to making this site accessible to all readers. The site
            supports keyboard navigation, screen readers, reduced-motion preferences,
            and multiple contrast modes (light, dark, and high-contrast).
          </p>
          <p>
            If you encounter an accessibility barrier, please contact us at
            <a href="mailto:finnoybu@gmail.com"> finnoybu@gmail.com</a> and we will
            work to resolve it promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="cookie-policy" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Cookie Policy</h2>
          <p>
            This site uses cookies and browser local storage to provide and
            improve the reading experience. Below is a summary of what we store
            and why.
          </p>
          <h3>Essential (always active)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Authentication cookies</strong> — set by our authentication
              system (Better Auth) on the <code>.finnoybu.com</code> domain so a
              single sign-in covers both fiction.finnoybu.com and memoirs.finnoybu.com.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Local storage</strong> — your reading preferences
              (theme, font size), scroll position, and cookie-consent acknowledgement
              are stored in your browser so they persist between visits.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not use cookies for advertising, retargeting, or cross-site
            tracking. If our use of cookies changes, this policy will be updated
            and the "last updated" date at the top of this page will
            reflect the change.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="disclaimer" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
          <p>
            "Finnoybu: Salt and Silence" is a work of historical
            fiction. While the novel draws on real nineteenth-century
            Norwegian maritime life for its setting and period detail, the
            characters and their interior lives are inventions of the
            author. References to named historical figures, if any, appear
            in fictionalized form and do not purport to represent their
            actual views or conduct.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="dmca" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>DMCA &amp; Takedown</h2>
          <p>
            If you believe content on this site infringes your copyright, please
            send a written notice to
            <a href="mailto:finnoybu@gmail.com"> finnoybu@gmail.com</a>
            including: identification of the copyrighted work, the infringing URL,
            your contact information, and a statement of good-faith belief.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="impressum" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <h2>Impressum</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Publisher:</strong> Finnoybu Press
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Responsible person:</strong> Ken Tannenbaum
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Contact:</strong>{' '}
            <a href="mailto:finnoybu@gmail.com">finnoybu@gmail.com</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
